==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sweetbread
<hw>Sweet"bread`</hw> <pr>(sw⟦emac⟧t"br⟦ecr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Either the thymus gland or the pancreas, the former
being called <stype>neck sweetbread</stype> or <stype>throat
sweetbread</stype>, the latter <stype>belly sweetbread</stype>. The
sweetbreads of ruminants, esp. of the calf, are highly esteemed as food.
See <er>Pancreas</er>, and <er>Thymus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The pancreas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sweet-breasted</ent>⟦br⟧
